## TL;DR: What Every 1.5ct Cushion Buyer Must Know First

The 1.5 carat cushion cut diamond ring is the cushion market's hidden sweet spot. Most buyers choose 1ct (accessible budget) or 2ct (statement size) and skip 1.5ct entirely — which is a mistake. At 7.5mm × 7.5mm face-up, the 1.5ct cushion delivers 90%+ of a 2ct's visual presence at a fraction of the 2ct natural price.

Lab at 1.5ct is where the economics become genuinely compelling: $1,422 for IGI E-VVS2 Excellent Cushion Modified versus ~$6,500 for natural GIA G-VS1. That $5,000 difference is not buying a better diamond — it is buying geological origin.

**Contrarian Truth — The Modified Brilliant Split at 1.5ct:** The 7.5mm face-up area of a 1.5ct cushion is the first size where the difference between a cushion modified brilliant (crushed ice — fine, uniform sparkle) and a cushion brilliant (chunky facets — distinct fire) is clearly visible without expert training. At 1ct, both sub-types look similar at a glance. At 1.5ct, they are plainly different aesthetic products — and most buyers purchase the modified brilliant by default without knowing there was a choice.

**Live price snapshot (Blue Nile {{year}}):**
- Lab 1.5ct IGI E-VVS2 Excellent Cushion Modified: **[$1,422](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28961887?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
- Lab 1.5ct GIA D-IF Ideal Cushion Modified: **[$2,909](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/26961413?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
- Natural 1.5ct GIA G-VS1 Ideal Cushion Modified: **~$6,500** ([browse current inventory](https://www.bluenile.com/diamonds/cushion-cut-diamonds?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational))

**→ The best entry point** for lab buyers is the [IGI 1.5ct E-VVS2 Excellent Cushion Modified at $1,422](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28961887?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — E colour, VVS2 clarity, Excellent cut, 7.5mm face-up, $469 less than a natural 1ct G-VS1 at $1,891. For natural buyers: GIA 1.5ct G-VS1 Ideal at ~$6,500 is the correct starting point.

