## What Is a 1.5 Carat Cushion Cut Diamond Ring?

A 1.5 carat cushion cut diamond ring combines a 1.5ct cushion-shaped diamond — approximately 7.5mm × 7.5mm face-up in standard square proportions — with an engagement ring setting. The 1.5ct size is meaningfully larger than the 1ct entry point (6.5mm × 6.5mm) and substantially smaller and more affordable than the 2ct tier (~8mm × 8mm). It is the cushion size most buyers overlook when they frame their options as "1ct or 2ct."

I'm **Farzana Hasan**, a GIA Expert. The [1.5 carat cushion cut diamond ring](/cushion-cut-diamond) occupies a unique position in the cushion cluster: large enough to command immediate attention at normal social distances, small enough to avoid the finger-dwarfing effect of a 3ct or the headline price of a [2 carat cushion cut diamond ring](/2-carat-cushion-cut-diamond-ring). At 1.5ct, both named concepts that define cushion buying — The Modified Brilliant Split and The Pillow Premium — reach their first clearly visible expression.

Below 1.5ct, these distinctions are subtle. At 1.5ct, they are obvious. What determines a successful purchase: choosing the sub-type first (The Modified Brilliant Split), understanding the exponential price jump from 1ct natural to 1.5ct natural, and recognising that the lab market at 1.5ct offers the most dramatic value argument in the entire cushion cluster.

Full credentials and methodology at **[Diamond Critics](https://diamondcritics.com/about-farzana/)**.

