## The Pillow Premium

The Pillow Premium — the systematic price premium cushion cuts carry over equivalent-quality princess cuts — is present at 1.5ct and more consequential in absolute dollars than at 1ct.

[![Cushion cut diamond engagement ring in rose gold solitaire with pavé band](https://ion.bluenile.com/sets/Jewelry/Photoshoot/Bluenile/BrioSuperImposeBox/Rings/502250/502250_M1_CSH_DIM_wht_0100CT_Y_Box3_004_1600X1600.jpg)](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings?ShapeID=Cushion&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)

At the [1 carat cushion cut diamond ring](/1-carat-cushion-cut-diamond-ring) tier, The Pillow Premium adds $200–$300 over an equivalent princess — real but manageable. At 1.5ct, the premium scales to $300–$500 in absolute dollars. A GIA 1.5ct G-VS1 Ideal princess typically runs $5,800–$6,200; the GIA 1.5ct G-VS1 Ideal cushion runs approximately $6,500 — an 8–12% premium.

**Why The Pillow Premium grows with carat weight.** Cushion cutting requires removing more diamond rough per finished carat than princess cutting. At 1.5ct, the rough crystal required is proportionally larger, and the cushion-specific waste in rounding the corners is more material in absolute terms than at 1ct. Simultaneously, demand for cushion cuts at 1.5ct is higher than at 1ct — buyers who have moved past the entry tier prioritise the cushion's distinctiveness over the princess cut's efficiency.

**The Pillow Premium's disappearance in the lab market.** In lab grown diamond production, The Pillow Premium at 1.5ct is negligible to non-existent. Lab production of cushion modified brilliants at 1.5ct is highly efficient, and the demand-driven premium that affects natural cushions does not translate to lab pricing. For lab buyers choosing between 1.5ct cushion and 1.5ct princess, the price difference is within $100–$200.

**Is The Pillow Premium worth it at 1.5ct?** Yes, for buyers who have genuinely chosen the cushion shape based on its visual character. The $300–$500 absolute premium at 1.5ct is the smallest it will be in dollar terms above the 1ct tier — at 2ct natural, it expands to $1,000–$2,000; at 3ct and above, to $5,000 and beyond. For a full analysis of how The Pillow Premium scales, see the [2 carat cushion cut diamond ring guide](/2-carat-cushion-cut-diamond-ring).

