*Filter to 1.5ct cushion on [Blue Nile](https://www.bluenile.com/diamonds/cushion-cut-diamonds?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) to see current live inventory and pricing — availability changes daily.*

**The natural 1.5ct price jump.** The step from 1ct G-VS1 ($1,891) to 1.5ct G-VS1 (~$6,500) is a 3.4× price increase for a 50% increase in carat weight. This is the diamond market's carat weight exponential: rarity increases sharply above 1ct, and the price premium per carat grows with it. A buyer who budgeted $2,000 for a natural 1ct cushion will need to triple that budget to maintain G-VS1 Ideal quality at 1.5ct.

**Natural 1.5ct colour guidance.** G colour at 1.5ct in a cushion modified brilliant is borderline for white metal settings — the 7.5mm face-up area exposes more body colour than 6.5mm. In platinum or white gold, F colour or above is the recommended minimum. In yellow gold or rose gold, G-H colour is appropriate — the warm metal reflection partially neutralises body warmth.

**The natural 1.5ct clarity minimum.** VS1 is the reliably safe clarity floor at 1.5ct — all VS1 cushion modified brilliants at this size are eye-clean without video verification. VS2 at 1.5ct requires HD video confirmation: inclusions that hide at 6.5mm can become visible at 7.5mm depending on placement and type. SI1 is not recommended without individual stone eye-cleanliness confirmation from the HD video.

> "The natural 1.5ct cushion market is where I have to be most direct with buyers about price reality. The jump from 1ct natural to 1.5ct natural is not 50% in cost — it is 200–250% for G-VS1 Ideal quality. Most buyers have not been told this before they begin comparing stones.
>
> My guidance at 1.5ct natural: if your budget is under $8,000 for the stone alone, start at G-VS1 Ideal and verify colour in your intended setting before committing. If your stone budget is under $5,000 total, the lab market is the correct path — not a compromise, but the superior financial decision." — Farzana Hasan, **[Diamond Critics](https://diamondcritics.com/about-farzana/)**

