## 1.5ct Cushion Cut Diamond Ring: Rose Gold

Rose gold is the metal most frequently paired with cushion cuts at 1.5ct, and the combination is particularly well-suited. The warm pink tone of rose gold creates visual contrast with the cool white brilliance of a D-F colour cushion modified brilliant's crushed ice pattern. The contrast makes both the metal and the stone appear more vivid.

For a 1.5ct cushion in rose gold, the ideal colour grade is F-G for natural stones. Rose gold reflects warmth into the pavilion of any stone, adding slight warmth regardless of the graded colour value. Paying the D-E colour premium in rose gold at 1.5ct is spending $1,000–$3,000 more for a colour upgrade the setting partially negates.

For the lab 1.5ct rose gold ring, the [IGI E-VVS2 Excellent at $1,422](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28961887?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is an excellent choice — E colour reads as white against rose gold without the D colour premium. Set in rose gold pavé, this creates the most-requested 1.5ct cushion ring aesthetic for under $2,500 total stone cost.

