> "For buyers considering a 1.5ct cushion because they cannot afford a 2ct natural but want something larger than a 1ct natural: stop that calculation and consider lab. The $1,422 IGI E-VVS2 lab cushion at 1.5ct costs less than a natural 1ct G-VS1 at $1,891. It is a better quality grade, a larger stone, and $469 less money.
>
> The only buyer for whom natural 1.5ct makes unambiguous sense is the buyer who has decided — consciously, after examining both options honestly — that natural origin is important to them independent of price. That is a valid decision. But it should be a deliberate one, not a default." — Farzana Hasan, **[Diamond Critics](https://diamondcritics.com/about-farzana/)**

