## Expert Summary

The 1.5 carat cushion cut diamond ring is the cushion cluster's most overlooked tier. Most buyers evaluate 1ct and 2ct as their two default options and skip 1.5ct without considering what it offers: 90%+ of the 2ct's visual presence at less than half the natural 2ct price, and one of the most compelling lab value arguments in the diamond market.

The two concepts that determine purchase quality at 1.5ct: The Modified Brilliant Split (7.5mm face-up is the first size where buyers can see the difference between crushed ice and chunky facets without expert help — choose your sub-type first, verify via HD video, never skip this step) and The Pillow Premium (cushion costs $300–$500 more than princess at 1.5ct natural — this is the smallest absolute Pillow Premium above the 1ct tier, and it should not drive buyers away from the cushion shape if cushion is the genuine preference).

The recommended purchase for most buyers is the [IGI 1.5ct E-VVS2 Excellent Cushion Modified at $1,422](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28961887?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). For buyers who want GIA certification with top grades on paper: the [GIA 1.5ct D-IF Ideal at $2,909](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/26961413?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). For buyers committed to natural origin: start at GIA G-VS1 Ideal (~$6,500) and verify colour in your intended metal before committing to a specific stone.

